title: SPEED SYSTEM FOR HONG KONG
description: Tech Mahindra supports HSBC's Speed System, a bidirectional file transfer application.
functions: The application manages file flow between multiple clients and HSBC Bank.
Inbound and outbound files are handled through protocols like HTTPS, FTPS, AS2, SFTP, etc.
I am responsible for maintaining smooth file flow, ensuring secure connectivity between peers, and generating daily reports for performance analysis.

title: EDW(Enterprises Data Wire House)
functions: Received Files from various sources are loaded into targeted tables.
This process is configured in Control M, a job scheduling tool.
In Core, Data Sets Files are created and loaded into tables.
Load process includes one-to-one, one-to-many, and many-to-many data mappings.
Once the Core process is completed, it triggers the PL process.
PL generates reports based on the processed data.
Reports provide insights and analysis of the data stored in the data warehouse.
techStack: React | JavaScript | Chakra UI | Firebase | CSS
